The « 4 in 1 » compilation concept was born in 1982 with the release of a C60 cassette named « 4 in 1 – Vol.1 ».
4 Belgian groups : Mécanique Végétale , Pseudo Code , Etat Brut and Human Flesh took part in the experiment, making a 15 minutes musical program and an artwork grouped in a A3 black & white poster.
It was one of the first « home-made » product initiated and coordinated by Alain Neffe.

Quickly after, the second volume including the participation of The Legendary Pink Dots , Subject , Glamour For Evening  and Bene Gesserit was issued.
This time it was a shared vinyl LP.
This LP was quickly out of stock and remains a collector item.

Incredibly enough,  in 2012 meaning 30 years later, the third volume was released by Eriek Van Havere on his famous EETAPES Label.
This time is was a shared CD, with the participation of Pseudo Code, BeNe GeSSeRiT, Messy Goes Insane and Human Flesh.

The concept is  seductive – 15 minutes is enough to catch the listener's attention and not long enough to be boring ... in the opposite, it opens your musical appetite !!!

Back to the roots, the Fourth volume  will be a C-60 cassette with  A3 size black & white poster.
This will be an INSANE Music label product with the participation of :
M.A.L., KOSMOSE , ALICE JUST and BeNe GeSSeRiT
A 100% « Home-made » product !



A short description of the bands :

- M.A.L.
This lonesome guitar player released his first cassette « Chemistry » in 1981 on Grafika Airlines and has never stopped since then to make music.
He is a multiple styles artist, going from minimal electronic, cosmic experimental to melodic New-Wave.
Daniel MALEMPRE was a member of the bands KOSMOSE, SIC (1970's), SUBJECT and HUMAN FLESH (1980's).

- KOSMOSE
This band was active from 1972 to 1979, playing a sort of psychedelic industrial music.
Ahead of their time ... this recording features the late Paul KUTZNER, Francis POURCEL
(SIC), Guy HINANT (Pseudo Code, SUB ROSA label) and Alain NEFFE (BeNe GesseRiT, Pseudo Code, Cortex, Subject, Human Flesh, I Scream, SIC (punk period), Japanese Genius).

- ALICE JUST
A new comer, using minimal synths to support her delicate and emotional lyrics.
For some of these recordings, she got a little help from Flavien Gillié (Final cut, etc) and Alain Neffe.
INSANE Music is very proud to introduce her works.

- BeNe GeSSeRiT
This duo (Benedict G. And B. Ghola) began in 1981 and never ceased releasing music on dozen of labels all around the world.
Their style is hard to define ; it may be perverted pop or rock, as well as emotional experimental or alien cabaret pastiche.
Benedict G. use to sing in French, broken English  and other invented languages giving to the voice an important role in the music.
